id: pm-nd08
title: "GH-253: invalid --type create error hardcodes .agents/pm path, ignoring active --pm-path"
description: ""
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags: []
created_at: "2026-06-16T17:15:13.625Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-16T19:40:35.506Z"
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-mpbb
resolution: Added resolveItemTypesFilePath; threaded resolved schema/types.json path into buildInvalidTypeError across create/update/config.
expected_result: Hint points at the configured tracker's schema/types.json.
actual_result: Hint hardcoded .agents/pm/schema/types.json regardless of --pm-path.
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-16T19:30:05.744Z",maintainer-agent,"Fixed: invalid --type create/update/config errors now thread the resolved schema/types.json path via new resolveItemTypesFilePath(pmRoot, schema) (runtime-schema.ts), so the hint reflects the active --pm-path instead of hardcoded .agents/pm. buildInvalidTypeHint/Error gained an optional typesFilePath param (falls back to .agents/pm default)."
close_reason: "Fixed: invalid --type error hint now reflects the active --pm-path."
body: "pm create --type <invalid> rejection message suggests 'pm schema add-type ... (writes .agents/pm/schema/types.json)' with a HARDCODED path, ignoring the active --pm-path. pm schema remove-type already reports the real configured path. Fix: thread the resolved pmRoot into the invalid-type error builder so the hint reflects the actual tracker path (and omits stale .agents/pm when a custom path is active)."
